in python calculate the average and standard deviation of a list of numbers
def main():
numbers = [3, 4, 5, 10, 12, 8]
average = sum(numbers)/len(numbers)
print("Average:", round(average, 2))
standard_deviation = math.sqrt((sum([i**2 for i in numbers]) - (average ** 2) * len(numbers)) / (len(numbers)-1))
print("Standard Deviation:", round(standard_deviation, 2))
